[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m (1) **Therapeutic-content-corpus-as-code lifecycle and crisis-screening-classifier and FDA-strategy-artifact and consent-language and mandatory-reporting-routing-policy and companion-pattern-avoidance-policy governance scaffolding underspecified despite explicit prose elevation.** The recipe correctly elevates therapeutic-content-corpus-as-versioned-governance-artifact-with-behavioral-health-clinical-leadership-signature-as-launch-gate, crisis-screening-classifier-as-separately-validated-pipeline-with-false-negative-rate-as-launch-gate, companion-pattern-avoidance-as-system-prompt-and-output-safety-and-sampled-review-architectural-floor, warm-handoff-workforce-capacity-as-architectural-primitive, mandatory-reporting-routing-policy-as-versioned-per-state-asset, FDA-strategy-artifact-as-regulatory-counsel-reviewed-versioned-asset, consent-language-as-versioned-asset-reviewed-by-mental-health-experienced-legal-counsel, and eligibility-check-policy-as-versioned-asset in multiple separate places. Despite this prose elevation, the architecture pattern, the diagram, and the pseudocode treat the multi-asset clinical-and-regulatory-policy governance as institutional-policy reference rather than as architectural primitives with explicit version-control discipline, sandbox testing against held-out support cases (including held-out crisis-presentation cases), staged rollout with per-content-and-per-classifier canary, rollback-on-regression, named ownership at the behavioral-health clinical leadership plus operations plus compliance plus regulatory team, per-asset-version stamping on every support-decision-record and crisis-event-record, annual review cadence, and per-state regulatory configuration. Recipe-acute and life-safety-acute amplification because the bot is the chapter's first life-safety-acute recipe and the bot's safety floor is bounded above by all eight artifacts simultaneously and because the bot approaches the FDA SaMD line with active regulatory exposure and because the documented incidents in the broader AI-companion category have been precisely the failure modes these governance artifacts are meant to prevent.
